caption: Pizza is delicious! Got a vegan pie. Quick to order online. Clean space and friendly staff. Forgot to snap a pic but it was sooo good!

The vegan pizza exceeded our expectations, given this place isn't a vegan spot. Really nice! Will def be ordering again. Great to have that option in this neighborhood.
Always hits the spot.

Gave an additional star because the pizza was okay, not outstanding though. Paid $3.25 for a pathetically small Sicilian slice. I was served by some guy who looked like he'd rather be dead than work there. Overall not a great experience for average tasting pizza. I definitely won't be coming back

I have to say if this is what real Italian pizza taste like I want to move to Italy.  The crust is no other crust I have ever had.  I come from Parkchester in the Bronx just to have this pizza.  Once you've had this pizza you are never going to want that non-authentic neighborhood pizza. Trust me just try it.

Unfortunately didn’t get to try a slice. Went in tonight. Two men working. Neither spoke to me. I said hi. The guy on my side of the counter pointed to the guy behind the counter who seemed to be washing dishes. I said hi to him, he ignored me. I waited said hey again, kind of annoyed and he pointed at the guy on my side of the counter I turned to him and said what’s up? He pointed at the guy behind the counter. I left. I don’t like to be played with, no one does

Usually really good pizza but lately they've been undercooking and sending like this white cheese on the regular pie when they had more of a darker NY cheese slice going. I prefer the latter but they're still quality and some of the best pizza in the neighborhood!
They offer a large range of delicious food. I enjoyed dining here. The employees are always super nice, prices are fair and the spot is always well organised.
Surprisingly crunch crust, I liked it though! The shop was cute, I would’ve lingered longer if not for covid.

My go-to pizza spot! Their regular pie is huge, delicious, and affordable if you pick it up in person. They've got a great range of toppings and the service is great.
I like Sicilian, costed 3.75
Love there vegan slice!

I'm from Connecticut, and its been 12 years since I ate a NY Slice pizza. and boy it was worth the wait! Mind you that pizza from Connecticut isn't really all there. Thats why I gave uncle Tony's pizza 5 stars!
Can’t Live without my Uncle Tony’s. Grandma Pie is my go-to, thank you!
Love happy hour
Best pizza I’ve had! The crust is impeccable. 10/10 would order again.
Best pizza I’ve have in Harlem

My neighborhood pizza place. I love the interior of this little shop, you can tell they put thought and care into making it a chill, welcoming space. The pizza is always great, with a stellar variety. Including vegan! Great place!
Absolutely perfect thin crust, delectable sauce, delightful cheesiness. New York pizza at its absolute best! Thank you all!
Best slice place in Harlem easy...

Grabbed a quick slice while I was in the area for work. I had never been to the upper west side and wasn’t familiar with local pizza shops. I was hoping to find something comparable to my Bushwick neighborhood pizza place, Archie's Pizza & Bar. I spotted Uncle Tony’s pizza sign and liked the blue pizza graphic, so I decided to check it out. The space is quaint, cool, minimal. Staff was friendly and fast. The Sicilian looked good but I went with the Bosco, which had wild mushrooms, ricotta, rosemary, mozzarella and truffle drizzle. It was quite tasty and I can tell they source quality ingredients. The slice was a decent size but I only had one. I would probably need another to feel satisfied. For the vegans out there, they have a vegan slice. If I'm ever in the area again, I’d stop through Uncle Tony's again.
So tastys and they have 2 slices for 5 bucks on weekends

(Translated by Google) The place is very small but the pizza is very tasty and the slice is huge. In front of the City College it is very easy to locate. It is better to buy takeaway pizza because the place is filled with few people so small it is, but the pizza is worth.  (Original) El lugar es muy pequeño pero la pizza es muy rica y el slice es enorme. Está frente al City college es muy facil de localizar. Es mejor comprar la pizza para llevar porque el lugar se llena con pocas personas por lo pequeño que es, pero la pizza vale la pena.
(Translated by Google) Good pizza  (Original) Buena pizza

Uncle Tony's is one of the only establishments in this neighborhood you can find Vegan Pizza. The establishment is clean and brand new. It seems to cater toward the college crowd of City University across the street, nonetheless great place to grab a slice. Like most pizza joints, there is no bathroom here! You'll have to go next door haha.
Horrible customer service. Sub par food.

Come later in the evenings, and they will not enforce the 5$ minimum for using credit cards. Otherwise, food is fantastic or simply have each slice be 5$. This was my only experience in the morning and shall come at night, as I normally do.
They have a nice happy hour and before-closing deal. The pizzas are fresh and delicious. Personal fave is the buffalo chicken.
Awesome. Really good pizza. Best I have had in a long time
Standard prices but a great restaurant (Fumo) to compliment this nice pizzeria. Bonus: They have vegan slices.
The best pizza
Great pizza and perfect for between classes.

One of the best pizza spots on the hill. Cozy storefront mostly serving Hamilton Heights, CUNY City College, Manhattanville MTA garage and various city posts throughout Hamilton Heights. The flavor and ingredients are primo. Been going to them since they opened. I DEPEND on these guys!
Best pizza in the Hamilton Heights area. The prices are a little higher than I like, but you get what you pay for.  Happy hour from 9-10p is better, affording beer and any slice for $6.
Good pizza
The pizza was amazing!!!must try it if your in town and yes the take card n cash to make any payments

I stepped in here looking for a quick bite and I’m so glad I did! Every one of their pizza options looked amazing but I chose the buffalo slice instead. Loved the crunchy chicken combined with the soft bread and cheese. The staff is also super friendly and it took less than a minute for my slice to be warmed up. They also have great happy hour specials.

The food was great! Pizza hot and fresh! Unfortunately I won't be ordering from them again though because my Capital Once credit card I used to purchase the food and my Discover credit card thats stored on file on my grub hub account were compromised after this purchase was made. Someone tried to use my cards at a corner store for almost $300. Luckily both credit card providers declined it as "suspicious activity" and both cards were shut down. Its annoying to have to wait 3-5 days to receive new cards and update merchants that I have automatic payments with, with my new card info. Ive now removed all cards stored on my grub hub account.

I left my credit card there by mistake and called them. They said they have it, so I said I would come back several days later to pick it up. They said OK. When I returned to pick it up, they said they cut it and threw it away.
The drink lids were over filled so be careful when you take a sip
Had a delicious brunch... and relaxing environment...
Different but good.
The price is reasonable considering the quality of food. I've always enjoyed their pizzas, and it's a step up from cheap dollar slice.
My go-to pizza place near CCNY
After 9pm every night, if you buy an alcoholic drink every slice you buy is only $1!!
The pizza was delicious and the owners were really nice with me! Congrats!
Great pizza. Worth  the money.
My favorite pizzas are the Bosco, cauliflower and chicken ranch.  Saturday and Sundays from noon till 4pm is an amazing happy hour deal of buy two for $5.

I like the place. However, the big dude with the messed up beard has a very insolent attitude. He’s the one that puts the pizza slices into the oven & hands them to you. It’s been more than once that he’s in a bad mood & treats customers (not just me) with utter disdain.
Honestly the best pizza I’ve ever had. And the workers were so great, accommodating, cute, sweet and DAMN, they can make amazing ‘za!!!

I love this spot. The vegan pizza is delicious! Yum yum. The atmosphere is nice too with the fake plants and art on the wall 👌 Workers are very kind as well. Oh and their music playlist is always on point. They should definitely learn how to make vegan buffalo cauliflower pizza 😍 or at least get vegan pepperoni. Nothing wrong with expanding their options. 😁💚

The pizza is delicious
The bosco pizza is delicious!

Great customer service, very friendly staff. On the whole the pizza was okay. The crust/dough used was excellent, heated to perfection.my only issue is a personal preference, I do not like coated/fried Chicken on chicken and ranch pizza. I prefer chicken to be grilled. I would absolutely go back again, but will try something different. I really like original artwork as decor.
Very crispy 👌
Awesome pizza
Awesome buffalo pizza, best I've tried.
Surprising toppings and flavors!  Soo good!

Update June 2, 2019: I had previously written a review based on the slice we got when we stopped by. Last night we ordered two pies. I was shocked at how sparse the toppings were! One of the pies we ordered was "The Supreme" which is supposed to have bacon, meatball, sausage, and jalapeno. We also added pepperoni on the whole pie. The total for that pie alone was $34.20! For that price, I would expect it to be overloaded with toppings. The jalapeno and pepperoni were sparse. I could barely discern the sausage and meatball. And I'm not convinced there was actually any bacon on it at all! There's a great pizzeria in New Haven (I have family there) that does a similar pizza for a lot less and then are not messing around with those toppings. I was expecting something similar if not more over the top for this price but we were sadly disappointed. I would never order this pizza again!  ****  No DiFara's (but what is) but it's a solid neighborhood slice. Haven't ordered a pie for delivery yet but was happy with pepperoni Sicilian slice we got when we walked in. Will definitely order from them in the future and am happy to have them in Hamilton Heights.
Great uptown option for a pie.

Fantastic pizza joint with delicious vegan slices that have melty (vegan) mozzarella cheese, marinara, and (vegan) pesto! Only thing I'd say is they put the slices in a touch too long so the crust was bordering on hard. I'd go back and tell them just to heat it up real quick.  Ooh and they also have a great happy hour on weekends from 11-4. 2 for $5 slices!
Best vegan slice in NYC and that's because it's a real pizza joint.

Have to go there and try the truffle mozzarella portobello mushroom pizza thin crispy delicious also try the cauliflower mushroom and purple onion another winner I haven't had pizza this good since I was in Brooklyn Driggs Pizza they're gone now it's two boots that's the last time pizza this good definitely worth going out of your way for not ordinary at all.
DELICIOUS

Ordered a Sicilian Pizza and 2 orders of Garlic Knots. They were out of Garlic Knots, so rather than contact us to let us know and possibly allow us to add a different item, they merely omitted them and refunded the price of the item.  Pizza arrived 10 minutes late; not a big deal.  Sicilian crust was stale, dry and chewy rather than crisp on the outside and light and airy inside and tasted like cardboard.  Called to complain and they suggested that we didn't know what Sicilian pizza was supposed to be. Oh, we know what it's supposed to be.  Get one at Joe's downtown and you'll enjoy everything that Uncle Tony's got wrong. Then they suggested that we should order something else next time.  We will; it will be something else from somplace other than Uncle Tony's.
AMAZING Taste & Quality Pizza!!
Great but not enough space

It's a pretty okay spot. Great location right across the street from City College but I think the prices are pretty high, especially for a place where the main customers are college students. Getting pizza catered for City College events of about 25-30 people will use up more than 1/3 of any club's or student association's annual event budget. It's very aesthetically pleasing inside the restaurant though and there is always great music playing. My main complaint is that there is only one type of vegan pizza and it is not the best. It's great in a pinch as the area doesn't have many easily accessible vegan friendly options...but there could be more variety with it.
Great Food, Great Service!
Great pizza.
Some of the best NY pizza, and definitely in the area. Cool lil place too.

I ordered a cheese pizza...they covered half with pepperoni. They didn’t let me keep the messed up pizza, then told me I could when I called and complained about waiting even longer. The cheese pizza arrived, but my free pizza was nowhere to be found. I hate this place and I’m never ordering from Uncle Tony’s again. 1 star is way too much.
Very clean place and delicious pizza with affordable price.

Uncle Tony's is by far one of the best uptown pizza slice restaurants. Their crust has flavor! I also found both the square slice and traditional pie slice to have an enjoyable balance of crunchiness and chewiness. They have a few interesting topping and style options available by the slice. Prices are reasonable, service is efficient.
We usually order from Papa John’s but decided on something different tonight...and I’m so glad we did!! Everything was so delicious and fresh!!
Awesome

Great place to enjoy different varieties of pizza. We had 2 cauliflower, bakers and chicken ranch. Bakers is  pepperoni pizza with thick crust whreas chicken ranch is a thin crust pizza with added bacon in addition to chicken. Cauliflower is a square pizza with total different taste. It had cauliflower, mushroom, onions and olives. My personal favorite is chicken ranch. We didn't know that it was happy hour. All 4 pieces cost only $10. Mouth watering. Will visit again

Really good pizza and for an affordable prize. I work around there and is my go-to lunch spot.

Cute clean place, nice staff. The pizza...Amazing!! One of the best I've had. (I'm a New Yorker so I've tried many pizzerias) The mushroom with truffle oil is my favorite. Sat & Sun 11am - 4pm they have a special, any 2 slices for $5. Def recommend this place.
Greet bites interesting slices

My super put me on to this place and I have to say, it's so good. To me, second best to Mama's Pizza. The inside is nice, not too large or too small. The decor is pleasant. The pizza itself, delicious! Had the regular slice and a supreme. Both left me wanting more. I love the fact that the supreme had the small pepperoni, for some reason, I fancy that to the regular sized pepperoni at other locations. This is now my go to spot whenever I'm in that area
Cheap, fast and easy place. A good place for a fast lunch
Uncle Tony... The best!
Good pizza at a good price. Friendly service. Limited options

For an ordinary slice place, it doesn't get much better. Prices are inexpensive, pizza is good, and it's a clean place. So far, I've had the regular slice, Sicilian slice, and vegan slice. THE VEGAN SLICE IS ACTUALLY GOOD! It's not just good if you're a vegan, I'm not a vegan, and I actually like it a lot and will continue to get it. Flavorful and not bad tasting in any way.

Delicious pizza 🍕that classic plain slice && they offer other options.. they work really hard and was tending to everyone fast and acknowledged everyone and was quick. Loved the service and definitely will come back 👍🏼👍🏼

I just wanna thank you guys for making a normal slice of NYC style pizza with quality ingredients. No hipster nonsense. No gimmicks. Just an honest to goodness slice of NYC style pizza with a lovely chewy and crispy crust and a perfect cheese/crust/sauce ratio. As a NYC and a fat Italian I give Uncle Tony's my highest recommendation  I get a tear to my eye every time I open the pizza box. It's always perfect, with just the right about of "sag" to the crust. It's worth the extra money. You guys have warmed my heart.
Best pizza in the neighborhood, by far.
Great price for great pizza

I just tried to eat my weight of the vegan slices. Fantastic pizza. The pesto was super creamy and the crust (my favorite part) was impeccable. Make sure you can the said to dip your crust in. You can substitute vegan cheese for the other pizzas but you have to order a whole pie. Next time, I'm calling ahead for a vegan Sicilian and some garlic knots!
Great pizza, very tasty. It’s my favorite spot for recharging my batteries, after late hours studying at City College.

I went to Uncle Tony's Pizza last night, and had a terrible experience. The women working behind the counter had a terrible attitude, and clearly took no pride in her job. When we were ready to order, we told her what we wanted, half regular half supreme, but she said we had to buy half supreme and half Sicilian, so they wouldn't have to make a new pizza, that cost us an extra $5 for the pizza we didn't want. When I asked her what it was, she had no idea, and then after reading the menu she just pointed at the pizza and said it's that. She couldn't tell us what drink flavors they had either. When we got The pizza, four of the pieces were completely black on the bottom. When we finished, we cleaned our own table, and threw away all our trash, except for the pizza box which wouldn't fit in the can, so we gave to her. This was such an inconvenience to her that she let out a very audible frustrated sigh as she came to take the box from us. In reality the unburnt pizza was very good, and I am very happy they used unbleached flour and organic tomatoes. Terrible service from the one employee paid to interact with us.
The Grandma Pie is probably the best pizza in the neighborhood!
Uncle Tony's is a much needed addition to the city college community. Pizza is ridiculously good and the place is beautiful

Delicious pizza worth returning to again and again; definitely one of the best in the neighborhood! There are a number of different options of pizza to choose from including vegan. The staff is friendly and quick.
Great food, dirt cheap. Bit of a small space, but as it's been getting cold, it's a little haven of warmth. Also, amazing, speedy service.
Really love their vegan pizza.  Quick service, decent prices, good music, just wish they would wear gloves at all times while handling the food!  :
Just walked in and out with a slice !!! This is what we needed in this neighborhood !!!! I love it!

Been working at City College for 16 years.  Finally.  FINALLY A GOOD PIZZA PLACE!  PRAISE THE LORD!  Place is small and busy at lunch time, so prepare to take out.  The Sicilian is to DIE FOR!  I usually hate Manhattan pizza, but I felt like I was in the Bronx.  Crisp, buttery crust, GENEROUS pepperoni, amazing sauce and gooey, stringy cheese.  Absolutely delicious!  Please support this place.  To my fellow CUNY staff and students, help them succeed!  Great pizza!  Strange it's called "Uncle Tony's!"
Best slice in Hamilton Heights!
Best pizza I've had in the neighborhood, and some of the best I've had in the whole city! Not pricey either
The Sicilian slice had great flavor and just the right mix of chewy and crunchy.

So far so good, great New York Style Pizza with a nice toasty crunchy crust and smoky flavor, not too greasy and pretty lightweight feeling eating it. Each slice is currently $2.50 which is a steal around this neighborhood now that so many businesses are opening up and is amazing due to the fact that there's only one other pizzeria that's been around for ages and only accepts cash. This place takes your debit or credit card at no minimum and is nice and clean.
